e multilingual nature of the Singapore-Malayan society through the speaking person while developing the central theme of the novel. The book maps out the verbal artistic representation of the speaking person and the correlation between speech and character in a multilingual environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMalaysian literature (English)xHistory and criticism. 0aMalaysian literature (English)--History and criticism. 0aSingaporean fiction (English)xHistory and criticism. 0aSingaporean fiction (English)--History and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh1 aPuthucheary, R. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPuthucheary, Rosaly J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTalib, Ismail S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102470708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106066830 cprintz978981230911240uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981230912940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789812309129423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789812309129/original  a978-3-11-060668-3  ISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-066300-6  ISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-102470-7  ISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKAL